What you have done is incomplete. You must use `SplitInstallStateUpdatedListener`.
There are 2 things that you need to ensure:
 1. Session id is same as yours.
 2. Status obtained is `SplitInstallSessionStatus.INSTALLED`.

When the above two points are ensured it is only then you can proceed with opening/accessing your dynamic module. 

I saw this question now but this should definitely work.

