The code is very weird. At first glance, I thought it used reflection to access `URLClassLoader` internals to add `myJar` to _an existing class loader_, but instead it uses it to add it to _a new class loader_. There&#39;s no reason to do that - you can just use [the `URLClassLoader` constructor][1] for that.

It should look something like this (untested because I am away from an IDE):

```java
URL jar = new File(&quot;C:/external-folder/my.jar&quot;).toURI().toURL();
URL[] urls = { jar };
new URLClassLoader(urls);
```

  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/net/URLClassLoader.html#%3Cinit%3E(java.net.URL%5B%5D)

