I can see 2 ways. They both rely on the fact that you can calculate the length of the current line in the StringBuilder this way:

`int currentLineLength = sb.length() - sb.lastIndexOf(&quot;\n&quot;);`


**1: The Stream way** 
- Add commas to each string except the last one
- try to add each token to the `StringBuilder`
  - If adding next token to the the current line in the StringBuilder is more than max, add line break
  - Add token

```
